```julia
function clean_column(col::AbstractString)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), [" ", "-"] => "_")
end
```

This function takes a `String` as input and returns a new string with the specified modifications. It first strips leading and trailing whitespaces using `strip()`, then lowercases the entire string using `lowercase()`. Finally, it replaces both spaces (`" "`) and hyphens (`"-"`) with underscores (`"_"`) using the `replace` function with a dictionary as its second argument.
